{
  "id": "numbers",
  "title": "Numbers",
  "order": 5,
  "summary": "Catalan numbers follow clear patterns — learn the system, not just the words.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "The numbers 1–10 are the foundation and must simply be memorised. From 11 onwards, patterns kick in that let you build any number."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "un / una",
          "english": "1",
          "note": "masculine / feminine"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dos / dues",
          "english": "2",
          "note": "masculine / feminine"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "tres",
          "english": "3",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "quatre",
          "english": "4",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "cinc",
          "english": "5",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "sis",
          "english": "6",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "set",
          "english": "7",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "vuit",
          "english": "8",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "nou",
          "english": "9",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "deu",
          "english": "10",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "11–15 are irregular and must be learned: onze, dotze, tretze, catorze, quinze. From 16 onwards the pattern is 'ten + and + unit': setze (16), disset (17), divuit (18), dinou (19)."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "onze",
          "english": "11",
          "note": "irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dotze",
          "english": "12",
          "note": "irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "tretze",
          "english": "13",
          "note": "irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "catorze",
          "english": "14",
          "note": "irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "quinze",
          "english": "15",
          "note": "irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "setze",
          "english": "16",
          "note": "set + ze"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "disset",
          "english": "17",
          "note": "deu + set"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "divuit",
          "english": "18",
          "note": "deu + vuit"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dinou",
          "english": "19",
          "note": "deu + nou"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "The tens are: vint (20), trenta (30), quaranta (40), cinquanta (50), seixanta (60), setanta (70), vuitanta (80), noranta (90). To combine, use 'i' (and): vint-i-un (21), trenta-dos (32), etc. Note: only 21–29 use 'i'; from 30+ the hyphen is used without 'i'."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "vint",
          "english": "20",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "vint-i-un",
          "english": "21",
          "note": "vint + i + un"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "vint-i-cinc",
          "english": "25",
          "note": "vint + i + cinc"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "trenta",
          "english": "30",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "trenta-dos",
          "english": "32",
          "note": "trenta + dos (no 'i')"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "quaranta",
          "english": "40",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "cinquanta",
          "english": "50",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "seixanta",
          "english": "60",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "setanta",
          "english": "70",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "vuitanta",
          "english": "80",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "noranta",
          "english": "90",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "Hundreds: cent (100), dos-cents / dues-centes (200), tres-cents (300)... Note that 200+ agree in gender: dos-cents metres but dues-centes persones. Mil (1,000) and milió (1,000,000) do not change for gender."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "cent",
          "english": "100",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dos-cents / dues-centes",
          "english": "200",
          "note": "masc / fem"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "cinc-cents",
          "english": "500",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "mil",
          "english": "1,000",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "un milió",
          "english": "1,000,000",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Ordinal numbers (first, second...) are used for dates, floors, and rankings. The most common ones: primer/primera (1st), segon/segona (2nd), tercer/tercera (3rd), quart/quarta (4th), cinquè/cinquena (5th)."
    }
  ],
  "practice": [
    {
      "id": "nu-p01",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "How do you say 17 in Catalan?",
      "options": [
        "disset",
        "setze",
        "dinou",
        "divuit"
      ],
      "answer": "disset",
      "explanation": "deu + set → disset."
    },
    {
      "id": "nu-p02",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "How do you say 25?",
      "options": [
        "vint-i-cinc",
        "vint-cinc",
        "dos-cinc",
        "cinc-vint"
      ],
      "answer": "vint-i-cinc",
      "explanation": "21–29 use vint-i-."
    },
    {
      "id": "nu-p03",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "You're buying 200 tickets (bitllets, masculine). Which form?",
      "options": [
        "dos-cents bitllets",
        "dues-centes bitllets"
      ],
      "answer": "dos-cents bitllets",
      "explanation": "Hundreds agree: dos-cents (m)."
    },
    {
      "id": "nu-p04",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "What is the Catalan for 'first' (masculine)?",
      "options": [
